        <p class="my-4">Following Scrum? Instead of the usual months, you can set your calendar to display sprints — 
            just tell it the start date and duration, and voilà! The entire year is divided into neat, 
            colour-coded sprints making it incredibly easy to:</p>
        <ul class="">
            <li class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Visualise your project timeline:</span> See how sprints stack up across the year.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Count sprints until key dates:</span> No more manual calculations or guessing.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Stay focused on agile goals:</span> The sprint-first layout keeps you in tune with your workflow.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="my-4"><a class="inline-flex items-center text-green-600 underline hover:no-underline" href="https://my.minicalendar.app">Try it now <ArrowRightIcon class="ms-2 size-4" /></a></p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="flex flex-wrap sm:flex-row my-20 sm:my-40">
    <div class="sm:w-2/3">
        <p class="text-3xl font-medium my-4">Track recurring activities</p>
        <p class="my-4"></p>
        <ul class="">
            <li class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Log Recurring Events:</span> Easily keep track of activities and events throughout the year.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Visual Spacing:</span> See how evenly your events are spread out over time.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Time Since Last Event:</span> Instantly check the number of days since your most recent event.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Event Totals:</span> View the total count of events logged for the year.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Activity Averages:</span> Calculate the average number of days between events for better planning.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="my-4"><a class="inline-flex items-center text-green-600 underline hover:no-underline" href="https://my.minicalendar.app">Log your first activity <ArrowRightIcon class="ms-2 size-4" /></a></p>
    </div>
